column5: Same friend who gave me the split cane pole, gave me 2 top water lures I have never seen the likes of.  They have a small "propeller" at the rear of the lure...(I know!! Lots of them do!) BUT the difference is that when the propeller turns...the long black wire legs MOVE ALSO!! Can't find anything on the web. Was wondering if anyone can identify them, as there are no markins on them. He said he got themk in the US but can't remember where.  Can only add 2 photos as that is max size. allowed but you will get the idea. Hopefully I uploaded then correctly.  Thanks for ANY info!  FT
reminisient of the old Helin " Fishcake " but they didn't have legs, are they maybe added on later?
Looks like something Fred Arbogast would have concocted is my initial guess....possibly something from the Heddon corp...

I too thought maybe Arbogast or Heddon but I can't find anything about them on any of those types of sites. Still looking on the web but nothing so far. Surely SOMEONE has seen 1 or something similar!  FT
A guy from another board found them Check out the video on the site. I am gonna have to make some of these.....MUSKY SIZE!!!  http://www.lurelore.com/crazyleg.html   FT
